import folium
import requests
import pandas

arrest_table = pandas.read_csv("https://cmsc320.github.io/files/BPD_Arrests.csv")

arrest_table = arrest_table[pandas.notnull(arrest_table["Location 1"])]

arrest_table[["lat", "long"]] = arrest_table["Location 1"].str.split(",", expand=True)
arrest_table["lat"] = arrest_table["lat"].str.replace("(", "", regex=True).astype(float)
arrest_table["long"] = arrest_table["long"].str.replace(")", "", regex=True).astype(float)
arrest_table.head()

#Part 3: Combining Parts 1 and 2

#taking a sample of the data since the table is so large
sample_data = arrest_table.sample(n=500)

#gender map will mark the male arrests in blue and the female ones in pink 
gender_map = folium.Map(location=[39.29, -76.61], zoom_start=11)
for index, row in sample_data.iterrows():
    #femlale = pink
    if (row['sex'] == 'F'):
        folium.Marker(
            location=[row['lat'], row['long']],
            icon=folium.Icon(color='pink',icon="none")
        ).add_to(gender_map)
    #male = blue
    elif (row['sex'] == 'M'): 
        folium.Marker(
            location=[row['lat'], row['long']],
            icon=folium.Icon(color='blue',icon="none")
        ).add_to(gender_map)
gender_map

import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')

#race map will mark the race of the arrests, 
#the races given with it's corresponding color:
# B: Race: Black, Color: black
# W: Race: White, Color: white
# A: Race: Asian, Color: yellow
# U: Race: Unknown, Color: red
# I: Race: American Indian or Alaskan, Color: brown
# H: Race: Hispanic, Color: orange

race_map = folium.Map(location=[39.29, -76.61], zoom_start=11)
for index, row in sample_data.iterrows():
    if (row['race'] == 'B'):
        folium.Marker(
            location=[row['lat'], row['long']],
            icon=folium.Icon(color='black')
        ).add_to(race_map)
    elif (row['race'] == 'W'): 
        folium.Marker(
            location=[row['lat'], row['long']],
            icon=folium.Icon(color='white')
        ).add_to(race_map)
    elif (row['race'] == 'A'): 
        folium.Marker(
            location=[row['lat'], row['long']],
            icon=folium.Icon(color='yellow')
        ).add_to(race_map)
    elif (row['race'] == 'U'): 
        folium.Marker(
            location=[row['lat'], row['long']],
            icon=folium.Icon(color='red')
        ).add_to(race_map)
    elif (row['race'] == 'I'): 
        folium.Marker(
            location=[row['lat'], row['long']],
            icon=folium.Icon(color='green')
        ).add_to(race_map)
    elif (row['race'] == 'H'): 
        folium.Marker(
            location=[row['lat'], row['long']],
            icon=folium.Icon(color='orange')
        ).add_to(race_map)
        
race_map

Analysis on Gender Map and Race Map: I marked the Baltimore map using 2 different ways. First, using only 500 enteries of the sample data (since the original data was too large), I marked all the male arrests in blue and the female arrests in pink. The results showed that there are way more male arrests since there was a lot more blue markers on the map than pink. There were still pink markers on the map, so females do get arrested, but not as much as males. In the second map, also only using 500 enteries, I colored the markers corresponding to the race. So if the race was black, the marker color was black, if the race was white, then the marker color was white, and so on explained above in my code comments. The results of this marked map showed that there are a lot of black race arrests. This marker color showed up the most in the map. The second most frequent color was white. So the white race was the second most frequent race arrested. Further research could let us know if Baltimore is a mainly black area, and could explain if this is why there are more black race arrests. There are some red markers on this map, which means that is an arrest of an unknown race person. Out of the 500 enteries in the data, there were no other race markers show in the race map I made.
